				<p>Seems like a reincarnation of what the Toyota Prius has been using for years. Only the Prius system looks a lot less complicated and better suited for hybrid vehicles and energy recovery. The Prius system is essentially a planetary gear (or differential) in which both the sun and planetary gear cogs are driven producing the same effect of a CVT, with reverse, without a clutch or friction system to interrupt torque. Check the link for an animation: <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wind.sannet.ne.jp/m_matsu/prius/ThsSimu/index_i18n.html">http://www.wind.sannet.ne.jp/m_matsu/prius/ThsSimu/index_i18n.html</a> </p>
