					        <div id="comment-22360" class="a_comment">
				<p>This is probably the most important invention I've seen yet on Gizmag. High-impact because it can be employed today. Excellent reporting too guys. </p>
<p></p>
<p>Yes, it does function similarly to the Prius system. However you have to appreciate what a gigantic leap it is for all vehicles, hybrid or not. For aircraft and boats it allows you to get rid of the variable-pitch propeller. </p>
<p></p>
<p>This may also represent a big blow to the Hybrid platform. It allows constant-speed running of the ICE; a primary benefit of hybrids. For ICE cars, it is a godsend that allows you lose not only the gears but the clutch as well. And the weight of hybrid batteries. </p>
<p></p>
<p>This is a really, really big deal. </p>
