				<p>No, not the holy grail. Reducing drive output speed with a power take-off shaft (PTO), control shaft or whatever you want to call it is an inefficient waste of torque, regardless of whether you use it to drive a generator to be later reclaimed as in the Prius application. The shimano 27 speed chain drive on my bicycle is more advanced than this, not to mention the Rohloff and Davinci hub gear transmission concepts which are more efficient. </p>
